race.comment: Great race as you'd imagine for the sprint series. THE MAGISTRATE (2) just missed in much tougher class fresh then gave a sight at Morphettville last time. Form good for this grade and will take beating third-up. FREE BEER (1) was a determined fresh-up winner then finished alongside THE MAGISTRATE in town last time. Much better drawn here and should feature as well. SOMAURUM (12) is much better than the last couple suggest. Was five deep throughout last time over the border but with a nice weight and draw in this she can find her best form. COOL THE JETS (4) has been out of the money recently including last time out when ninth over 1000m at Morphettville Parks six weeks ago, beaten 3.5 lengths. This much more suitable. Drawn for a soft run and is sure to be thereabouts.
